{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"8f419704-f04c-4e7a-a316-6567b1176780","content":"Here's the step-by-step plan for your .NET 10 SDK on headless Linux:\n\n---\n\n### 1. Discover Required Versions\n\n```bash\n# See what MAUI workload is available for your SDK\ndotnet workload search maui\n\n# Check what's already installed\ndotnet workload list\n```\n\n### 2. Install the MAUI Workload\n\n```bash\nsudo dotnet workload install maui-android\n# (use 'maui' if you want all platforms, but maui-android is sufficient for Android-only)\n```\n\nThis pulls in the Android SDK bindings, but **not** the Android SDK itself.\n\n### 3. Find the Required Android API Level & Build-Tools\n\n```bash\n# After workload install, check what Android version MAUI targets:\ncat ~/.dotnet/packs/Microsoft.Android.Sdk.Linux/*/Sdks/Microsoft.Android.Sdk/Sdk/Versions.props 2>/dev/null \\\n  || dotnet new android -o /tmp/_probe && grep TargetFramework /tmp/_probe/*.csproj\n```\n\nFor .NET 10 MAUI, this is typically **Android API 35** (Android 15). Your project's `$(TargetFramework)` (e.g., `net10.0-android35`) confirms the exact level.\n\n### 4. Install OpenJDK 17\n\n```bash\nsudo apt-get update && sudo apt-get install -y openjdk-17-jdk\nexport JAVA_HOME=/usr/lib/jvm/java-17-openjdk-amd64\n```\n\nAndroid Gradle/build-tools require JDK 17 (not 21).\n\n### 5. Install Android SDK Command-Line Tools\n\n```bash\nexport ANDROID_HOME=$HOME/android-sdk\nmkdir -p \"$ANDROID_HOME/cmdline-tools\"\n\n# Download latest command-line tools\ncurl -fsSL https://dl.google.com/android/repository/commandlinetools-linux-11076708_latest.zip \\\n  -o /tmp/cmdline-tools.zip\nunzip -q /tmp/cmdline-tools.zip -d \"$ANDROID_HOME/cmdline-tools\"\nmv \"$ANDROID_HOME/cmdline-tools/cmdline-tools\" \"$ANDROID_HOME/cmdline-tools/latest\"\n```\n\n### 6. Install the Right SDK Components\n\n```bash\nexport PATH=\"$ANDROID_HOME/cmdline-tools/latest/bin:$PATH\"\n\n# Accept licenses first\nyes | sdkmanager --licenses\n\n# Install components matching your MAUI target\nsdkmanager \\\n  \"platform-tools\" \\\n  \"platforms;android-35\" \\\n  \"build-tools;35.0.0\"\n```\n\n**How to find the exact `build-tools` version:** run `sdkmanager --list | grep build-tools` and pick the latest for your API level.\n\n### 7. Set Environment Variables\n\n```bash\nexport ANDROID_HOME=$HOME/android-sdk\nexport JAVA_HOME=/usr/lib/jvm/java-17-openjdk-amd64\nexport PATH=\"$ANDROID_HOME/cmdline-tools/latest/bin:$ANDROID_HOME/platform-tools:$PATH\"\n```\n\n### 8. Build\n\n```bash\ndotnet build -f net10.0-android -c Release\n# or to produce an APK/AAB:\ndotnet publish -f net10.0-android -c Release\n```\n\n---\n\n**Key version-matching rules:**\n| Component | How to determine version |\n|---|---|\n| MAUI workload | Must match your .NET SDK major version (`dotnet workload search`) |\n| Android API level | From your `TargetFramework` in `.csproj` (e.g., `android35`) |\n| Build-tools | Latest available for that API (`sdkmanager --list`) |\n| JDK | 17 — required by current Android toolchain |","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"f67a49a5-8db0-4f6f-91ff-52fa0fd468af","outputTokens":937,"requestId":"9BD6:21A8FE:61884A2:6CAF65C:69EC0DF4"},"id":"f847f8ee-1274-41c4-9e57-042654aa590f","timestamp":"2026-04-25T00:42:46.777Z","parentId":"39d3cdf1-76be-44ce-b31f-3ae7e26b9674"}
